# Copilot Instructions for Spring Boot Microservice

This repository follows a standard Spring Boot microservice architecture.

When generating code in this repository, follow these rules.

## Architecture

Use layered architecture:

Controller → Service → Repository → Database

Rules:
- Controllers handle HTTP requests only.
- Business logic belongs in the Service layer.
- Repository layer uses Spring Data JPA.

## API Design

- Do not expose JPA entities in REST APIs.
- Always use DTO objects.
- Use ResponseEntity in controllers.
- Follow REST conventions.

Example endpoints:

GET    /api/orders
GET    /api/orders/{id}
POST   /api/orders
PUT    /api/orders/{id}
DELETE /api/orders/{id}

## Dependency Injection

Use constructor injection with Lombok.

Example:

@Service
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class OrderService {

    private final OrderRepository repository;

}

## Logging

Use SLF4J logging.

Example:

log.info("Processing order {}", orderId);

## Testing

Use:

- JUnit 5
- Mockito

Follow Arrange → Act → Assert pattern.

## Validation

Use Bean Validation:

@NotNull
@NotBlank
@Email

## Error Handling

Use global exception handling:

@RestControllerAdvice
public class GlobalExceptionHandler {

}



